\s Psalm CXIX \\ The Power and Comfort of the Word of God
\q1 \c 119 \v 1 Happy they whose life is blameless,
\q2 Who walk by the law of the Lord.
\q1 \v 2 Happy they who keep His charges,
\q2 And seek Him with all their hearts;
\q1 \v 3 Who also work no unrighteousness,
\q2 But in Thy ways they walk.
\q1 \v 4 Thou Thyself hast appointed Thy precepts
\q2 To be kept with diligence.
\b
\q1 \v 5 O to be steadily guided
\q2 In the keeping of Thy statutes!
\q1 \v 6 Then unashamed shall I be,
\q2 When I look towards all Thy commandments.
\q1 \v 7 I will thank Thee with heart unfeigned,
\q2 When I learn Thy righteous judgments.
\q1 \v 8 I will observe Thy statutes:
\q2 O forsake me not utterly.
\b
\q1 \v 9 How can a young man keep his life pure?
\q2 By giving heed to Thy word.
\q1 \v 10 With all my heart have I sought Thee,
\q2 Let me not stray from Thy commandments.
\q1 \v 11 In my heart have I treasured Thy word,
\q2 To keep from sinning against Thee.
\q1 \v 12 Blessed art Thou, O Lord;
\q2 Teach Thou me Thy statutes.
\q1 \v 13 With my lips have I rehearsed
\q2 All the judgments of Thy mouth.
\q1 \v 14 I delight in the way of Thy charges,
\q2 More than in riches of all sorts.
\q1 \v 15 I will muse upon Thy precepts,
\q2 And look unto Thy paths.
\q1 \v 16 In Thy statutes I delight,
\q2 I will not forget Thy word.
\b
\q1 \v 17 Grant that Thy servant may live,
\q2 And I will observe Thy word.
\q1 \v 18 Open mine eyes, that I see
\q2 Wondrous things out of Thy law.
\q1 \v 19 But a guest am I on the earth:
\q2 Hide not Thy commandments from me.
\q1 \v 20 My soul is crushed with longing
\q2 For Thine ordinances, at all times.
\q1 \v 21 Thou dost rebuke the proud, the accursed,
