\q1 \v 23 Though princes sit plotting against me,
\q2 Thy servant will muse on Thy statutes.
\q1 \v 24 Thy charges are my delight,
\q2 They are my counsellors.
\b
\q1 \v 25 My soul cleaves to the dust;
\q2 Revive me, as Thou hast promised.
\q1 \v 26 I told of my ways, Thou madest answer;
\q2 Teach Thou me Thy statutes.
\q1 \v 27 Grant me insight into Thy precepts,
\q2 And I will muse on Thy wonders.
\q1 \v 28 My soul melteth away for sorrow;
\q2 Raise me up, as Thou hast promised.
\q1 \v 29 Put the way of falsehood from me,
