\q1 \v 30 I have chosen the way of fidelity,
\q2 Thine ordinances I long for.
\q1 \v 31 I cleave unto Thy charges:
\q2 O put me not, Lord, to shame.
\q1 \v 32 I will run in the way of Thy commandments,
\q2 For Thou givest me room of heart.
\b
\q1 \v 33 Teach me, O Lord, the way of Thy statutes,
\q2 And I will keep it unto the end,
\q1 \v 34 Instruct me to keep Thy law,
\q2 And I will observe it with all my heart.
\q1 \v 35 Guide me in the path of Thy commandments,
\q2 For therein do I delight.
\q1 \v 36 Incline my heart to Thy charges,
\q2 And not unto greed of gain.
\q1 \v 37 Turn away mine eyes from vain sights,
\q2 Revive me by Thy word.
\q1 \v 38 Confirm to Thy servant the promise
\q2 Which is given to those that fear Thee.
\q1 \v 39 Remove the reproach which I dread,
\q2 Because Thy judgments are good.
\q1 \v 40 Behold, I long for Thy precepts.
\q2 Quicken Thou me in Thy righteousness.
\b
\q1 \v 41 Visit me, Lord, with Thy l.ove
