\q1 \v 46 I will speak of Thy charge before kings,
\q2 And will not be ashamed thereof.
\q1 \v 47 Thy commandments are my delight,
\q2 I love them exceedingly.
\q1 \v 48 I will lift up my hands to Thy commandments,
\q2 And muse upon Thy statutes.
\b
\q1 \v 49 Remember Thy word to Thy servant,
\q2 On which Thou hast made me to hope.
\q1 \v 50 This is my comfort in trouble,
\q2 That Thy word giveth life unto me.
\q1 \v 51 The arrogant utterly scorn me,
\q2 But I have not declined frbin Thy law.
\q1 \v 52 When I think of Thy judgments of old,
\q2 O Lord, I take to me comfort.
\q1 \v 53 I am seized with glowing anger
\q2 At the wicked who forsake Thy law.
\q1 \v 54 Thy statutes have been to me songs
\q2 In the house of my pilgrimage.
\q1 \v 55 I remember Thy name in the night,
\q2 O Lord and observe Thy law.
\q1 \v 56 My (happy) lot hath been this,
\q2 That I have kept Thy precepts.
\b
\q1 \v 57 My portion art Thou, O Lord:
\q2 \v 1 have promised to keep Thy words.
\q1 \v 58 I entreat Thee with all my heart;
\q2 Grant me Thy promised favour.
\q1 \v 59 I have thought upon my ways,
\q2 And turned my feet to Thy charges.
\q1 \v 60 I hasted and tarried not
\q2 To give heed unto Thy commandments.
\q1 \v 61 Though the godless have wound their cords round me,
\q2 I have not forgotten Thy law.
\q1 \v 62 At midnight I rise to praise Thee
