\q1 \v 63 With all them that fear Thee I company,
\q2 Aiid with those that observe Thy precepts.
\q1 \v 64 The earth, Lord, is full of Thy kindness;
\q2 Teach Thou me Thy Statutes.
\b
\q1 \v 65 Well hast Thou dealt with Thy servant,
\q2 As Thou hast promised, O Lord.
\q1 \v 66 Teach me discretion and knowledge,
\q2 For I have believed Thy commandments.
\q1 \v 67 Till trouble came I was a wanderer,
