\q2 From the lip that is false
\q2 And the tongue that is crafty.”
\b
\q1 \v 3 What shall He give unto thee,
\q2 Thou tongue that art crafty?
\q1 What yet shall He give unto thee?
\q1 \v 4 Arrows of warrior, sharpened,
\q2 With glowing broom coals together.
\b
\q1 Woe is me that I sojourn in Meshech,
\q2 That I dwell by the tents of Kedar.
\q1 Already too long have I dwelt
\q2 Among men who hate peace.
\q1 As for me, I am peace altogether:
\q2 But the moment I speak,
\q2 They are for war.
\s Psalm CXXI \\ The Omnipotent Keeper
