\q2 Within thy gates, O Jerusalem.
\b
\q1 \v 3 O Jerusalem, built once again
\q2 Like a city without breach or gap,
\q1 \v 4 Unto thee do the tribes go on pilgrimage,
\q2 Even the tribes of the Lord,
\b
\q1 As the law hath ordained for Israel,
\q2 There to give thanks to the Lord.
\q1 \v 5 There once stood thrones of justice
\q2 Even thrones of the household of David.
\b
\q1 \v 6 Pray that all may be well with Jerusalem,
\q2 And well with those that love thee,
\q1 \v 7 Well within thy ramparts,
\q2 And well within thy palaces.
\b
\q1 \v 8 For the sake of my brethren and friends,
\q2 I will wish thee now prosperity:
\q1 \v 9 For the sake of the house of the Lord
\q2 Our God, I will seek thy good.
\s Psalm CXXIII \\ A Prayer for the Divine Pity
\q1 \c 123 \v 1 I Lift up mine eyes unto Thee,
\q2 Who art throned in the heavens.
\q1 \v 2 Behold, as the eyes of a servant
\q2 Turn to the hand of his master,
